deviation statement is not working for grouping:

Module:
```
module m {
  container c {
    uses g;
  }
  grouping g {
    leaf l {
      type string;
    }
  }
}
```
Deviation module:

```
module d {
  deviation /m:c/m:l {
    deviate not-supported;
  }
}
```

cmd$ pyang -f yin m.yang --deviation-module=d.yang

```xml
<container name="c">
    <uses name="g"/>
  </container>
  <grouping name="g">
    <leaf name="l">     >>>>>>>>>>>>> NO DEVIATION APPLIED
      <type name="string"/>
    </leaf>
  </grouping>
```

When I try to use TinyDB on an existing JSON like this one :
`{
    "_default": [
        value1,
        value2,
        ...
    ]
}`

It does not work but when I try on an empty json, TinyDB generates a json looking like this : 
`{
    "_default": {
        "1": value1,
        "2": value2,
        ...
    }
}`

Why does TinyDB uses an object with indexes and not a simple array ? Is it possible to configure TinyDB to use an array ?

