It's possible to define decorators at the url level or the http method level.  If a decorator is shared by all methods, but one method wants to add another and the decorator is defined there, then it will get duplicated and executed twice.

e.g.

```python
router.create_routes('example', 'example.yaml', {
    '/example/': {
        'decorators': [authenticate_user],

        'get': {
            'logic': get_example,
        },
        'post': {
            'decorators': [authenticate_user, validate_params],
            'logic': create_example,
        },
    }
})
```

The above example will call `authenticate_user` twice when hitting the POST endpoint.

