With Django 1.10 MIDDLEWARE can contain functions (first example in https://docs.djangoproject.com/en/1.10/topics/http/middleware/#writing-your-own-middleware). But function is_middleware_class called by check_middleware (https://github.com/jazzband/django-debug-toolbar/blob/master/debug_toolbar/apps.py#L66) expects that middleware is class.

Possible change - current code:
return issubclass(middleware_cls, middleware_class)

working code:
return isinstance(middleware_cls, type) and issubclass(middleware_cls, middleware_class)

Dear Pybind11 developers, here is another 2.2 regression issue (exact same code was working at a22dd2d 

Right now it seems not possible to bind member function which access was lifter to `public` with `using` declaration. Please see minimal example and error message below.

Thanks,

```C++
#include <pybind11/pybind11.h>

struct Base
{
	void foo() {}
};

class Child : private Base
{
public:
	using Base::foo;
};


PYBIND11_PLUGIN(example) {
    pybind11::module m("example", "pybind11 example plugin");

	pybind11::class_<Child>(m, "Child")
        .def("foo", &Child::foo);

    return m.ptr();

	Child c; c.foo();
}
```

Error:
```
/home/benchmark/src/pybind11/include/pybind11/pybind11.h:1000:93: error: cannot cast private base class 'Base' to 'Child'
auto method_adaptor(Return (Class::*pmf)(Args...)) -> Return (Derived::*)(Args...) { return pmf; }
                                                                                            ^
/home/benchmark/src/pybind11/include/pybind11/pybind11.h:1078:25: note: in instantiation of function template specialization 'pybind11::method_adaptor<Child, void, Base>' requested here
        cpp_function cf(method_adaptor<type>(std::forward<Func>(f)), name(name_), is_method(*this),
                        ^
access-lifting.cpp:20:10: note: in instantiation of function template specialization 'pybind11::class_<Child>::def<void (Base::*)()>' requested here
        .def("foo", &Child::foo);
         ^
access-lifting.cpp:8:15: note: declared private here
class Child : private Base
              ^~~~~~~~~~~~
1 warning and 1 error generated.
```

